-- PRESS DIGEST - Bulgaria - Jan 14
-- 
-- Tue Jan 14, 2014 01:35AM EST
-- None



SOFIA, Jan 14 (Reuters) - These are some of the main stories in Bulgarian newspapers on Tuesday. Reuters has not verified these stories and does not vouch for their accuracy.

- The leader of Bulgarian Socialist European Parliament deputies, Ivailo Kalfin, has resigned from his post, citing differences with the Socialist party differences in a move which analysts say may split the ruling party. (24 Chasa, Trud, Monitor, Duma, Capital Daily, Standart, Presa) - President Rosen Plevneliev approached the Constitutional Court to rule the new 20 percent charge on wind and solar power producers saying it was breaching the principles of rule of law and free economic initiative. (24 Chasa, Trud, Presa, Capital Daily, Monitor, Duma)  - The intercity bus service providers threatened with a general strike as of February if the state did not take steps to curb the gray services in the sector. (24 Chasa, Duma, Standart, Presa)